    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="1437"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1437">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/394.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Spanish Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Spanish Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 5, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: The Spanish Minister in Mexico
                    telegraphs me under yesterday’s date that the Constitutionalists who have
                    occupied San Luis Potosi are enforcing loans from the Spanish residents of that
                    town and are confiscating cattle from their ranches with the purpose of
                    exporting it, probably to the United States.</p>
                <p>I should esteem it a very great favor if you could exercise your good offices in
                    order to obtain a proper treatment for my countrymen in that town.</p>
                <p>Believe me [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Juan Riaño</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
